            I was going to say that, if that is the case, it says more about the Minister than it does about me and the intention behind my amendment.</p><p>
            I end where I started: my concern is the protection of children, so that they receive appropriate sex education. I shall carefully read what the Minister and other noble Lords have said. I shall do what I can to empower parents to make a judgment about sex education and its appropriateness, whether it is homosexual and/or heterosexual sex education.</p><p>
